  "cells": [
    {
      "id": "cs-intro-md-1",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "source": "# C# in Venus Notebooks\n\nVenus supports **C#** cells via `dotnet-script` — the .NET scripting tool.\n\n## Setup (one-time)\n1. Install the [.NET SDK](https://dot.net) (free, Windows / macOS / Linux)\n2. Install dotnet-script: `dotnet tool install -g dotnet-script`\n3. Restart Venus\n\n## Cell mode\nClick the mode button on any code cell to cycle through: **JShell → Java → JS → C# → F#**\n\n## Built-in helpers\n```csharp\nVenusHtml(\"<b>bold</b>\");   // render HTML in output\nVenusDisplay(myObject);      // Console.WriteLine shorthand\nVenusTable(myList);          // ASCII table for any IEnumerable\n```\n\n> Install NuGet packages in the **Packages → NuGet** tab — they are auto-injected into every C# cell.",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false
    },
    {
      "id": "cs-intro-1",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "csharp",
      "source": "//@ anchor: hello-world-in-c\n//@ description: Hello World in C#\n// Hello World in C#\nConsole.WriteLine(\"Hello from Venus Notebooks!\");\nConsole.WriteLine($\".NET version: {Environment.Version}\");\nConsole.WriteLine($\"OS: {Environment.OSVersion}\");",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false,
      "anchor": "hello-world-in-c",
      "description": "Hello World in C#"
    },
    {
      "id": "cs-intro-md-2",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "source": "## Variables and Types\n\nC# is statically typed. Use `var` for type inference.",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false
    },
    {
      "id": "cs-intro-2",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "csharp",
      "source": "//@ anchor: value-types-strings-and-interpolation\n//@ description: Value types, strings, and interpolation\n// Value types, strings, and interpolation\nvar name    = \"Venus\";\nvar version = 1.0;\nint year    = DateTime.Now.Year;\nbool isAwesome = true;\n\nConsole.WriteLine($\"Project: {name} v{version}\");\nConsole.WriteLine($\"Year: {year}, Awesome: {isAwesome}\");\n\n// String methods\nstring sentence = \"  Hello, World!  \";\nConsole.WriteLine(sentence.Trim().ToUpper());\nConsole.WriteLine($\"Length: {sentence.Trim().Length}\");",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false,
      "anchor": "value-types-strings-and-interpolation",
      "description": "Value types, strings, and interpolation"
    },
    {
      "id": "cs-intro-md-3",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "source": "## Collections and LINQ\n\n`System.Linq` is included automatically — use it for powerful data queries.",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false
    },
    {
      "id": "cs-intro-3",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "csharp",
      "source": "//@ anchor: list-and-linq\n//@ description: List and LINQ\n// List and LINQ\nvar scores = new List<int> { 85, 92, 78, 95, 88, 73, 96, 81, 69, 90 };\n\nvar passing   = scores.Where(s => s >= 75).ToList();\nvar avg       = scores.Average();\nvar top3      = scores.OrderByDescending(s => s).Take(3).ToList();\n\nConsole.WriteLine($\"All scores: {string.Join(\", \", scores)}\");\nConsole.WriteLine($\"Passing (>=75): {string.Join(\", \", passing)}\");\nConsole.WriteLine($\"Average: {avg:F1}\");\nConsole.WriteLine($\"Top 3: {string.Join(\", \", top3)}\");",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false,
      "anchor": "list-and-linq",
      "description": "List and LINQ"
    },
    {
      "id": "cs-intro-md-4",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "source": "## Classes and Records\n\nC# supports full OOP. Use `record` for immutable data types.",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false
    },
    {
      "id": "cs-intro-4",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "csharp",
      "source": "//@ anchor: record-types-c-9-perfect-for-data\n//@ description: Record types (C# 9+) — perfect for data\n// Record types (C# 9+) — perfect for data\nrecord Product(string Name, string Category, decimal Price, int Stock);\n\nvar inventory = new List<Product> {\n    new(\"Laptop\",    \"Electronics\", 999.99m,  15),\n    new(\"Notebook\",  \"Stationery\",    3.49m, 200),\n    new(\"Monitor\",   \"Electronics\", 349.00m,  22),\n    new(\"Pen Pack\",  \"Stationery\",    8.99m, 150),\n    new(\"Keyboard\",  \"Electronics\",  79.99m,  40),\n};\n\n// LINQ query syntax\nvar electronics = inventory\n    .Where(p => p.Category == \"Electronics\")\n    .OrderByDescending(p => p.Price)\n    .ToList();\n\nConsole.WriteLine(\"Electronics (by price):\");\nforeach (var p in electronics)\n    Console.WriteLine($\"  {p.Name,-12} ${p.Price,8:F2}  (stock: {p.Stock})\");\n\nConsole.WriteLine($\"\\nTotal inventory value: ${inventory.Sum(p => p.Price * p.Stock):N2}\");",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false,
      "anchor": "record-types-c-9-perfect-for-data",
      "description": "Record types (C# 9+) — perfect for data"
    },
    {
      "id": "cs-intro-md-5",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "source": "## VenusTable Helper\n\nUse `VenusTable()` to render any `IEnumerable` as an ASCII table.",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false
    },
    {
      "id": "cs-intro-5",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "csharp",
      "source": "//@ anchor: employee\n//@ description: Defines Employee type\nrecord Employee(string Name, string Dept, int YearsExp, decimal Salary);\n\nvar team = new List<Employee> {\n    new(\"Alice\",  \"Engineering\", 5, 95000m),\n    new(\"Bob\",    \"Design\",      3, 72000m),\n    new(\"Carol\",  \"Engineering\", 8, 120000m),\n    new(\"Dave\",   \"Marketing\",   2, 65000m),\n    new(\"Eve\",    \"Engineering\", 4, 88000m),\n};\n\nVenusTable(team);\n\nvar avgByDept = team\n    .GroupBy(e => e.Dept)\n    .Select(g => new { Dept = g.Key, Count = g.Count(), AvgSalary = g.Average(e => e.Salary) })\n    .OrderBy(x => x.Dept);\n\nConsole.WriteLine(\"\\nAverage salary by department:\");\nforeach (var row in avgByDept)\n    Console.WriteLine($\"  {row.Dept,-15} {row.Count} engineers  avg: ${row.AvgSalary:N0}\");",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false,
      "anchor": "employee",
      "description": "Defines Employee type"
    },
    {
      "id": "cs-intro-md-6",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "source": "## Pipeline Annotations\n\nC# cells support the same `//@ anchor:` and `//@ depends:` annotations as JShell cells.\n\n```csharp\n//@ anchor: loadData\n// ... load data ...\n```\n\n```csharp\n//@ depends: loadData\n// runs after loadData\n```\n\nSee **csharp-201** for a full pipeline walkthrough.",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false
    }
  ],
